Explanation:

The problem requires finding the minimum number of bit changes needed to make n equal to k. We can solve this by using a while loop to iterate until n becomes equal to k. In each iteration, we perform a bitwise AND operation (n & (n - 1)) to clear the least significant set bit in n. This operation takes O(log(n)) time complexity. The solution uses a constant space complexity (O(1)) since we only need a single variable to store the result. The energy implications are low since the algorithm operates on integers and performs bitwise operations, which are computationally efficient.

